HTTP correlation is only half the story. Incidents often cross async boundaries: API request enqueues work, worker consumes later, worker publishes another message, and eventually a notification goes out. If you drop identity at the queue edge, your trace breaks exactly where debugging gets hardest.

In this part, we extend the same correlation model from earlier posts into background jobs and message-driven processing.

